President Trump visited Snap-On Tools in Kenosha, Wisconsin to sign an executive order titled "Buy American, Hire American." The order aims to protect American workers and promote the use of American-made goods. Trump stated that the federal government will strictly uphold Buy American laws and minimize the use of waivers and exemptions. The order also calls for a crackdown on foreign bidders that use cheap, subsidized goods to win contracts. Additionally, Trump mentioned the need to enforce Hire American rules to prioritize American workers and end visa abuses. The President also discussed plans for tax reform, healthcare, and infrastructure. He criticized NAFTA and promised to make changes to the trade agreement. Trump emphasized the importance of American craftsmanship and the need to restore the American Dream.